olive oil
1 cucumber
½ fresh chilli  (optional)
1 carrot
2 clove garlic
1 head cos lettuce
1 packet pork mince
1 packet Ssamjang Paste
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tsp brown sugar
1 drizzle sesame oil
¼ cup water
1 packet roasted peanuts
¼ cup vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 bunch Asian Greens

• Thinly slice cucumber. In a small bowl, combine vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt.
• Add cucumber to the pickling liquid with just enough water to cover the cucumber. Set aside.

• Grate the carrot.
• Roughly chop Asian greens. Finely chop garlic. Trim the end of cos lettuce, then separate the leaves. Thinly slice fresh chilli (if using).

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add carrot and Asian greens and cook until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat, then add ssamjang paste, oyster sauce, the brown sugar, a drizzle of sesame oil and the water. Stir to combine.

• Drain pickled cucumber.
• Using a rolling pin or base of a saucepan, crush roasted peanuts in their packet (or finely chop if you'd prefer!).
• Spoon some garlic and ssamjang pork mince into each lettuce cup.
• Top with chilli, pickled cucumber and nuts to serve. Enjoy!